			<text><![CDATA[










In situ burning is an easy method to remove oil from the sea. It can, however, lead to a number of problems.
- ignition of oil (volatile parts evaporate fast)
- maintenance of combustion of slick
- air pollution (generation of large quantities of smoke)
- sinking of residues
- safety risks
]]></text>
